The paper deals with deep learning frameworks for image translation and manipulation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training and domain adaptation, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the manipulation of images, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of disentangled features, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
